  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `Geth/v1.9.9-stable-01744997/linux-amd64/go1.13.4`\r\nOS & Version: `Linux`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nBlock Download Speed: >= 1MB/s\r\n\r\n- 900+ Peer Count\r\n- Gigabit link\r\n- NVME Storage\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nBlock Download Speed: ~1MB/s\r\n- 900+ Peer Count\r\n- Gigabit link\r\n- NVME Storage\r\n\r\n**EDIT**\r\n\r\n- Up to 1200 Peers. Averaging about 4 MB/s  (12/29)\r\n- Up to 1800 Peers. Averaging about 7 MB/s (12/29)\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behavior\r\n\r\n`geth --cache 32768  --syncmode full --gcmode archive --maxpeers 4096 --metrics --metrics.influxdb .... `\r\n\r\n#### Background\r\nI've been doing a lot of research trying to figure out how to increase the speed of the block downloads but have not been able to find anything besides a few suggestions referencing an increase to the max peer count. Could someone please fill in my lack of knowledge as to what may be causing this? \r\n\r\nIn theory, I should be able to fully saturate a Gigabit line, no?\r\n",
